(1174, 130, 'descriptif_mission', '<b>Lentic\'s coaching approach</b> has the advantage both of surveying the functioning modes operating in organizations and their possible evolution, while paying due attention to the power games and conflicts inevitably shaping such an evolution.  Indeed, it is mandatory to take the diversity of viewpoints into account, the underlying values guiding the persons concerned, the weight of existing structures, the history of the organization, etc.\r\n\r\nLentic\'s in-house coaching takes this twofold orientation, and relies both on long-standing practice of organizational development and on participative management.  It aims to assist the current teams in surveying the existing processes, practices, procedures and tools as regards management and organization. It helps identify areas for improvement or progress with the view of reducing the gap between the current and desired situation for the sake of greater overall efficiency and sustains their implementation.'),
